cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG

Reasoning: The paper deals with image and video processing, specifically the task of recovering an image or video that has been collapsed along a dimension. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of convolutional neural networks as functional approximators suggests a machine learning (cs.MM) component to the work. The probabilistic model and variational inference strategy also suggest an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) component. Finally, the evaluation of the method on several datasets suggests a focus on machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
